\par }\pard \ltrpar\ql \li0\ri0\sa180\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af4 \ltrch\fcs0 \f46\kerning0\insrsid2443561\charrsid10639628 \hich\af46\dbch\af31505\loch\f46 
ModGroups is a feature that has been in xEdit for a long time, but has gotten very little attention in the past.
\par \hich\af46\dbch\af31505\loch\f46 This version totally overhauls the ModGroups support, adding many new features as well as providing complete\hich\af46\dbch\af31505\loch\f46  UI integration for creating, editing and managing ModGroups.
\par \hich\af46\dbch\af31505\loch\f46 
A ModGroup is a way to tell xEdit that certain (non-winning) overrides of a record can be hidden (because the still visible versions account for all the changes already). By hiding away these versions they no longer participate in conflict detection which
\hich\af46\dbch\af31505\loch\f46  can be used to prevent false positives from showing up.
\par \hich\af46\dbch\af31505\loch\f46 A ModGroup can never hide the winning override or the original master record.
\par \hich\af46\dbch\af31505\loch\f46 A setup where all real conflicts have been resolved by patch\hich\af46\dbch\af31505\loch\f46 \hich\f46 es and all false positives hidden by ModGroups will show an empty navigation treeview after applying a \'93\loch\f46 
\hich\f46 Filter to show conflicts\'94\loch\f46 . With this as the starting point, adding one new mod to an existing setup with 100\hich\f46 \rquote \loch\f46 s of mods will result in only the conflict\hich\af46\dbch\af31505\loch\f46 \hich\f46 
s caused by the addition of that new mod to show up when running \'93\loch\f46 \hich\f46 Filter to show conflicts\'94\loch\f46 
. This makes it very easy then to adjust the load order, created targeted patches to resolve real conflicts, and finally again create new ModGroups to hide away any\hich\af46\dbch\af31505\loch\f46  f\hich\af46\dbch\af31505\loch\f46 alse positives.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\ql \li0\ri0\sa180\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\outlinelevel2\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af4\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f46\fs28\ulth\kerning0\insrsid2443561\charrsid10639628 \hich\af46\dbch\af31505\loch\f46 New ModGroup Selection dialog

\par }\pard \ltrpar\ql \li0\ri0\sa180\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af4 \ltrch\fcs0 \f46\kerning0\insrsid2443561\charrsid10639628 \hich\af46\dbch\af31505\loch\f46 
When the background loader is complete, a new ModGroup Selection dialog is shown. This dialog is very similar to the new Modules Selection dialog and has most of its features.
\par \hich\af46\dbch\af31505\loch\f46 The dialog is based on a treeview, so you can directly expand the individual ModGroups to see their contents.
\par \hich\af46\dbch\af31505\loch\f46 You can filter the treeview to more easily find a specific ModGroup.
\par \hich\af46\dbch\af31505\loch\f46 A system for saving and loading presets is available.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\ql \li0\ri0\sa180\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\outlinelevel2\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af4\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f46\fs28\ulth\kerning0\insrsid2443561\charrsid10639628 \hich\af46\dbch\af31505\loch\f46 
