Create delta patch using\'85\'94
\par }\pard \ltrpar\ql \li0\ri0\sa180\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af4 \ltrch\fcs0 \f46\kerning0\insrsid2443561\charrsid10639628 \hich\af46\dbch\af31505\loch\f46 \hich\f46 A \'93\loch\f46 \hich\f46 delta patch\'94\loch\f46 
 is a module containing only the records that have changed between two versions of another module.
\par \hich\af46\dbch\af31505\loch\f46 \hich\f46 It is, effectively, the reverse of \'93\loch\f46 \hich\f46 Merge into Master\'94\loch\f46 \hich\f46 . If you have two versions of a module and produce a delta patch, then using the \'93\loch\f46 \hich\f46 
Merge into Master\'94\loch\f46  process of merging the delta patch into the first version of the module will result in the 2nd versi\hich\af46\dbch\af31505\loch\f46 on of the module.
\par \hich\af46\dbch\af31505\loch\f46 Creating a delta patch works similar \hich\af46\dbch\af31505\loch\f46 \hich\f46 to using \'93\loch\f46 \hich\f46 Compare to\'85\'94\loch\f46 \hich\f46 . After loading the old version of a module normally, the \'93
\loch\f46 \hich\f46 Create delta patch using\'85\'94\loch\f46  function asks for a newer version of the same module and the name of the to be created delta patch.
\par \hich\af46\dbch\af31505\loch\f46 It will then make a copy of the newer version into the data folder, using the specified name and .esu as extension (= Elder Scrolls Update, an extension that TES4Gecko introduced for delta patches).
\par \hich\af46\dbch\af31505\loch\f46 \hich\f46 This copied file will then be loaded using the same method as \'93\loch\f46 \hich\f46 Compare to\'85\'94\loch\f46 . Any record existing in the o\hich\af46\dbch\af31505\loch\f46 
ld version of the module and not in this new version will be copied and then flagged as deleted. Any record that is identical (using the same rules as ITM detection) between the two modules will be removed from the delta patch.
\par \hich\af46\dbch\af31505\loch\f46 This leaves the delta patch with only the records that have changed between the two versions of the module.
\par \hich\af46\dbch\af31505\loch\f46 It is recommended that the delta patch is saved and xEdit closed after creating it.
\par \hich\af46\dbch\af31505\loch\f46 \hich\f46 Like with \'93\loch\f46 \hich\f46 Compare to\'85\'94\loch\f46  last folder will be remembered (even across session).
\par \hich\af46\dbch\af31505\loch\f46 One of the mos\hich\af46\dbch\af31505\loch\f46 t important uses of a delta patch is when a module that another module uses as master has been updated.
\par \hich\af46\dbch\af31505\loch\f46 Suppose you have ModA and ModB, and a CompatPatchAB. ModA got updated and you want to figure out if CompatPatchAB must be updated.
\par \hich\af46\dbch\af31505\loch\f46 Create a delta patch between the old and new version of ModA, then restart xEdit and load: ModA, DeltaPatchA, ModB, CompatPatchAB.
\par \hich\af46\dbch\af31505\loch\f46 It is now easily possible to go through the records in DeltaPatchA (which contains only the records that have been changed in the updated version \hich\af46\dbch\af31505\loch\f46 
of ModA) and see side-by-side the old values in ModA, the new values in ModA, and the values in CompatPatchAB. Wherever a value has changed between ModA and DeltaPatchA, this value can be dragged over from DeltaPatchA to CompatPatchAB.
\par \loch\af46\dbch\af31505\hich\f46 \'93\loch\f46 \hich\f46 Create delta patch using\'85\'94\loch\f46  can also be used to turn an .esp replacer into a patch.esp (rename outside xEdit after creating it) which can be used on top of the original .esp.
\par \hich\af46\dbch\af31505\loch\f46 This is especially useful in cases where for the same original .esp there are two or more .esp replac\hich\af46\dbch\af31505\loch\f46 ers with different functions that you normally can\hich\f46 \rquote \loch\f46 
t use together. By changing the .esp replacers into patch.esps they can be used at the same time together with the original .esp. (May require the creation of another patch if there are conflicts between \hich\af46\dbch\af31505\loch\f46 
these different patches that need to be resolved.)
\par }\pard \ltrpar\ql \li0\ri0\sa180\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\outlinelevel1\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af4\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f46\fs32\ulth\kerning0\insrsid2443561\charrsid10639628 \hich\af46\dbch\af31505\loch\f46 
.esu as fully supported module file extension
